N2  - A recent study by Mimouni et al. shows that late gestation exposure to anti-Mullerian hormone (AMH) results in transgenerational transmission of a polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS)-like phenotype in mice. Altered DNA methylation underlies transmission and was also observed in women with PCOS. Epigenetics-based therapy reversed some PCOS-like phenotypic traits when applied to F3 female mice. Copyright © 2021 The Author(s). Published by Elsevier Ltd.. All rights reserved.
