A1  - Capuzzo, Martina
A1  - Donno, Valeria
A1  - La Marca, Antonio
Y1  - 2020//
N2  - The differential diagnosis of anovulatory disorders is actually based on serum gonadotrophin and estradiol levels. However, several other markers have been proposed. The purpose of this review was to underline the role of anti-Mullerian hormone (AMH) as a possible marker in differential diagnosis of the anovulatory diseases and its use as a predictive marker of prognosis. In this article we discuss clinical and experimental evidences actually existing in literature and we suggest new potential clinical application of AMH.
